Revlon Consumer Products Corp. Key Developments

Lorenzo Delpani Announces Not to Stand for Re-Election as Board Member of Revlon, Inc. and Revlon Consumer Products Corp
Apr 22 16
Revlon, Inc. and Revlon Consumer Products Corporation filed with the SEC on March 4, 2016, the company and Lorenzo Delpani entered into a Transition and Separation Agreement and Release on March 1, 2016 in connection with the transition of his duties and responsibilities as the company's former President and Chief Executive Officer. On April 21, 2016, the company and Mr. Delpani entered into an amendment to the TSA. In connection with the TSA Amendment, the parties have agreed that Mr. Delpani will not stand for re-election to serve as a member of company's Board at Revlon's 2016 annual stockholders' meeting scheduled to be held on June 9, 2016 and will also cease to serve as a member of Revlon Consumer Products Corp.'s Board as of that date.


Revlon Consumer Products Corporation Announces Executive Changes
Apr 12 16
On April 11, 2016, the board of directors of Revlon Inc. (Revlon and together with its subsidiaries, including, without limitation, Revlon Consumer Products Corporation (RCPC), the company), elected Juan R. Figuereo as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Revlon and RCPC effective as of April 12, 2016. Mr. Figuereo succeeds Mr. Roberto Simon in such position, whose resignation from the company was effective on February 29, 2016. Mr. Figuereo, 60, most recently served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of NII Holdings Inc. from October 2012 through October 2015.


Revlon Consumer Products Corp. Announces Executive Changes
Mar 28 16
Revlon Consumer Products Corporation elected Fabian T. Garcia as the Company's President and Chief Executive Officer, effective April 15, 2016. Mr. Garcia was also appointed to serve as a member of Revlon Inc.'s and RCPC's Boards of Directors, effective April 15, 2016. Mr. Garcia replaces Lorenzo Delpani, who served as the Company's President and Chief Executive Officer from November 2013 through March 1, 2016. Prior to joining the Company, Mr. Garcia served in senior executive positions at the Colgate-Palmolive Company, including most recently as its Chief Operating Officer, Global Innovation and Growth, Europe/South Pacific & Hill's Pet Nutrition, a position he held since 2010, with expanded responsibility for Hill's Pet Nutrition beginning in 2012.


